description:
Bug 3666 - Code Completion Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)

Under certain circumstances code assist eats too much code. When adding a parameter to the baz call in the bar method, the code assist replaces more code than necessary. 

Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the enclosed class.
2. In the bar method, add a parameter to the baz call.

Expected behavior:
The code should only replace the necessary code for the parameter addition.

Observed behavior:
The code assist replaces more code than necessary. The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

I would rather it gave me

baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {
   void bar(X x) {
      baz(x.foo());
   }
   int foo() {
      return 5;
   }
   void baz(int i, int j) {
   }
}
